<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 14:27:40 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>新图像显示这颗小行星实际上是两块连体的太空岩石。它们形成一个花生形状的物体，称为“接触二进制”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-images-reveal-that-this-asteroid-is-actually-two-conjoined-space-rocks-that-form-a-peanut-shaped-object-called-a-contact-binary-180989090/</link><description>日本隼鸟二号航天器飞越该行星时发现了这颗小行星的奇怪形状。探测器收集的数据也将有助于保护地球免受潜在威胁的太空岩石的影响</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 21:21:25 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-images-reveal-that-this-asteroid-is-actually-two-conjoined-space-rocks-that-form-a-peanut-shaped-object-called-a-contact-binary-180989090/</guid></item><item><title>波士顿市发现了已知最古老的自由美国黑人墓碑之一，他与马萨诸塞州首府同名</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-city-of-boston-discovered-one-of-the-oldest-known-gravestones-of-a-free-black-american-who-shared-a-name-with-the-massachusetts-capital-180989088/</link><description>他又名塞巴斯蒂安，于 1729 年去世，与塞缪尔·亚当斯、约翰·汉考克和保罗·里维尔合葬。他的一生讲述了美国革命前北方奴隶制与自由的故事</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 20:56:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-city-of-boston-discovered-one-of-the-oldest-known-gravestones-of-a-free-black-american-who-shared-a-name-with-the-massachusetts-capital-180989088/</guid></item><item><title>“就像玻璃工厂的爆炸”：弗兰克·盖里曾经装饰摩天大楼大堂的七吨重“冰阵”办公桌即将拍卖</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/like-an-explosion-in-a-glass-factory-frank-gehrys-seven-ton-icehenge-desk-that-once-graced-a-skyscraper-is-up-for-auction-180989087/</link><description>这张桌子是为芝加哥内陆钢铁大厦设计的，由十几块锯齿状的绿色玻璃制成</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 18:23:36 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/like-an-explosion-in-a-glass-factory-frank-gehrys-seven-ton-icehenge-desk-that-once-graced-a-skyscraper-is-up-for-auction-180989087/</guid></item><item><title>难道是本王毒害了他的兄弟？一项新的 DNA 分析可能会解开数百年的美第奇家族之谜</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-this-duke-poison-his-brother-a-new-dna-analysis-may-solve-the-centuries-old-medici-mystery-180989086/</link><description>研究人员在弗朗切斯科一世·德·美第奇的骨头中发现了疟疾的证据，使他们“以科学的确定性”辩称，导致他于 1587 年死亡的是疾病，而不是砷。</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 17:05:02 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-this-duke-poison-his-brother-a-new-dna-analysis-may-solve-the-centuries-old-medici-mystery-180989086/</guid></item><item><title>北冰洋可能已经过了一个可能损害食物网并加剧气候变化的关键临界点</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-arctic-ocean-may-have-passed-a-crucial-tipping-point-that-could-harm-food-webs-and-worsen-climate-change-180989083/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，海冰消失似乎引发了硝酸盐营养物的下降，影响了构成海洋食物链基础并吸收大气二氧化碳的微小生物体</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 15:36:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-arctic-ocean-may-have-passed-a-crucial-tipping-point-that-could-harm-food-webs-and-worsen-climate-change-180989083/</guid></item><item><title>我们的祖先喜欢贝壳饰品，就像尼安德特人一样。新研究表明这是跨物种共享文化的标志</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/our-ancestors-loved-shell-trinkets-just-like-neanderthals-new-research-suggests-its-a-sign-of-shared-culture-across-species-180989085/</link><description>根据在地中海沿岸石灰岩洞穴中发现的文物，科学家认为这两个物种可能具有相似的生存策略、石器技术和象征传统</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 14:26:56 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/our-ancestors-loved-shell-trinkets-just-like-neanderthals-new-research-suggests-its-a-sign-of-shared-culture-across-species-180989085/</guid></item><item><title>生活在东地中海的抹香鲸似乎已经发展出一种与西方不同的方言</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/sperm-whales-living-in-the-eastern-mediterranean-sea-seem-to-have-developed-a-distinct-dialect-from-those-in-the-west-180989084/</link><description>所有地中海抹香鲸都被认为是同一个文化群体的一部分，可以通过独特的滴答声或尾声模式来识别。但录音表明东方生物使用西方鲸鱼尾声的加速版本</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/sperm-whales-living-in-the-eastern-mediterranean-sea-seem-to-have-developed-a-distinct-dialect-from-those-in-the-west-180989084/</guid></item><item><title>澳大利亚海滩上有奇怪的球体被冲上岸。当局称它们可能是“太空球”——火箭中的空燃料容器</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/strange-spheres-washed-ashore-on-an-australian-beach-authorities-say-theyre-probably-space-balls-empty-fuel-vessels-from-a-rocket-180989082/</link><description>这些闪亮的物体——每个物体的大小大约是篮球的两倍——从 7 月 3 日开始出现。当局最初担心它们是危险的，但后来确定它们很可能是安全的太空垃圾。</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 21:15:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/strange-spheres-washed-ashore-on-an-australian-beach-authorities-say-theyre-probably-space-balls-empty-fuel-vessels-from-a-rocket-180989082/</guid></item><item><title>人们认为高大的树木更容易受到干旱的影响。但东南亚的这些高耸植物已经适应了有效地输送水</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/tall-trees-were-thought-to-be-more-vulnerable-to-drought-but-these-towering-plants-in-southeast-asia-have-adapted-to-move-water-efficiently-180989075/</link><description>一项新的研究发现，巨大的龙脑香树具有特殊的适应性，可以将水分输送到最高的树枝，这挑战了它们更容易屈服于干燥条件的假设</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 19:29:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/tall-trees-were-thought-to-be-more-vulnerable-to-drought-but-these-towering-plants-in-southeast-asia-have-adapted-to-move-water-efficiently-180989075/</guid></item><item><title>泰国铁器时代墓地发现一对 2000 年前的金戒指，其中一枚刻有印度文字</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-pair-of-2000-year-old-gold-rings-one-engraved-with-indian-script-was-discovered-in-an-iron-age-burial-ground-in-thailand-180989081/</link><description>该雕刻似乎引用了印度或吠陀占星学中的“吉祥”星座</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 19:19:19 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-pair-of-2000-year-old-gold-rings-one-engraved-with-indian-script-was-discovered-in-an-iron-age-burial-ground-in-thailand-180989081/</guid></item><item><title>这颗巨大的行星可能在其恒星死亡后幸存下来。詹姆斯·韦伯太空望远镜刚刚发现大气层</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-giant-planet-survived-the-death-of-its-star-the-james-webb-space-telescope-just-found-its-atmosphere-180989077/</link><description>对 WD 1856 b（一颗紧密围绕白矮星运行的气态巨行星）的新观测，为太阳在大约 50 亿年后死亡后木星和土星可能发生的情况提供了预览。</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 19:09:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-giant-planet-survived-the-death-of-its-star-the-james-webb-space-telescope-just-found-its-atmosphere-180989077/</guid></item><item><title>你能猜出纸莎草碎片或彩绘陶瓷的起源吗？一名大学生将大都会博物馆的开放访问数据库变成了在线游戏</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/can-you-guess-the-origins-of-papyrus-fragments-or-painted-ceramics-a-college-student-turned-the-mets-open-access-database-into-an-online-game-180989080/</link><description>如果您认为自己是一名艺术史爱好者，请通过 Anthropeum 来测试一下您的聪明才智。该游戏从大都会艺术博物馆的开放获取档案中提取十张图像，并挑战玩家识别每件文物的时间和原产地</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 17:09:01 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/can-you-guess-the-origins-of-papyrus-fragments-or-painted-ceramics-a-college-student-turned-the-mets-open-access-database-into-an-online-game-180989080/</guid></item><item><title>机器人蟑螂可以帮助寻找自然灾害的幸存者。新型潜水服让昆虫能够扩大水下搜索范围</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cyborg-cockroaches-could-help-find-survivors-of-natural-disasters-new-diving-suits-allow-the-insects-to-expand-their-search-underwater-180989066/</link><description>此前，研究人员制造了电子植入物来控制蟑螂的运动，以执行搜救任务。现在，他们制作了可提供氧气的 3D 打印套装，让这些生物能够在水下生存长达三个小时</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 16:01:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cyborg-cockroaches-could-help-find-survivors-of-natural-disasters-new-diving-suits-allow-the-insects-to-expand-their-search-underwater-180989066/</guid></item><item><title>海洋保护协会摄影比赛中的 11 张野生动物照片展示了地球水域的奇观</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-11-wildlife-images-from-the-ocean-conservancys-photography-contest-showcase-the-wonder-of-earths-waters-180989069/</link><description>该非营利组织的年度竞赛以海豹、企鹅和鱼类为特色，以激发人们对世界海洋的关爱</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2026 22:15:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-11-wildlife-images-from-the-ocean-conservancys-photography-contest-showcase-the-wonder-of-earths-waters-180989069/</guid></item><item><title>在加州科学中心举行新展览之前，以独特的垂直展示方式观看“奋进号”航天飞机</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-space-shuttle-endeavour-in-a-unique-vertical-display-before-its-new-exhibition-launches-at-the-california-science-center-180989073/</link><description>今年 11 月，洛杉矶新塞缪尔·奥辛航空航天中心的游客将看到“准备发射”的“奋进”号，配有火箭助推器和燃料箱</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2026 19:21:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-space-shuttle-endeavour-in-a-unique-vertical-display-before-its-new-exhibition-launches-at-the-california-science-center-180989073/</guid></item><item><title>早期开花植物可能依赖恐龙吃它们的肉质果实并传播它们的种子</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/early-flowering-plants-may-have-relied-on-dinosaurs-to-eat-their-fleshy-fruits-and-spread-their-seeds-180989076/</link><description>根据火山灰保存的化石，这些被称为被子植物的植物开始产生相对较大、蓝莓大小的果实，比之前认为的要早数百万年</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2026 19:12:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/early-flowering-plants-may-have-relied-on-dinosaurs-to-eat-their-fleshy-fruits-and-spread-their-seeds-180989076/</guid></item><item><title>一次新的探险将创建极地沉船的 3D 数字孪生，这些沉船与竞逐南极的竞争对手探险家的航行有关</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-new-expeditiion-will-create-3d-digital-twins-of-polar-shipwrecks-tied-to-voyages-of-rival-explorers-who-raced-to-the-south-pole-180989074/</link><description>罗伯特·法尔肯·斯科特率领“特拉诺瓦”号探险船和欧内斯特·沙克尔顿率领“探索”号船探险队，但这两位探险家都未能在南极洲中心插上第一面旗帜</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2026 17:44:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-new-expeditiion-will-create-3d-digital-twins-of-polar-shipwrecks-tied-to-voyages-of-rival-explorers-who-raced-to-the-south-pole-180989074/</guid></item><item><title>饥饿的科莫多龙如何让科学家们确定我们像霍比特人一样的小表亲可能根本没有那么聪明</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-a-hungry-komodo-dragod-led-scientists-to-determine-our-small-hobbit-like-cousins-probably-werent-that-smart-after-all-180989078/</link><description>新的研究表明，“弗洛勒斯人”可能并没有在弗洛勒斯岛上狩猎大型动物或使用火，这表明这种小脑物种并不像曾经假设的那样“行为先进”</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2026 15:31:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-a-hungry-komodo-dragod-led-scientists-to-determine-our-small-hobbit-like-cousins-probably-werent-that-smart-after-all-180989078/</guid></item><item><title>观看今年天文学年度摄影师大赛中捕捉宇宙奇观的十幅壮观图像</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-ten-spectacular-images-from-this-years-astronomy-photographer-of-the-year-contest-that-capture-the-wonders-of-the-universe-180989065/</link><description>竞赛入围名单上的这些照片揭示了我们头顶上非凡的天体，无论是在深空还是在离家较近的地方</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-ten-spectacular-images-from-this-years-astronomy-photographer-of-the-year-contest-that-capture-the-wonders-of-the-universe-180989065/</guid></item><item><title>人工智能生成的亚历山大·汉密尔顿在本周末于波士顿开幕的美国金融博物馆谈论经济学</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-ai-generated-alexander-hamilton-chats-about-economics-at-the-museum-of-american-finance-opening-this-weekend-in-boston-180989071/</link><description>该博物馆始于纽约，多年来一直没有永久展览空间，描绘了美国金融机构的历史和影响力</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 21:28:51 GMT</p